libvarnam
------------------------------------------
libvarnam is a cross platform, self learning, open source library which support
transliteration and reverse transliteration for Indian languages. At the core
is a C shared library providing algorithms and patterns for transliteration.
libvarnam has a simple learning module built-in which can learn words to
improve the transliteration experience.

Runtime requirements:
  cygwin-2.11.2-1
  libsqlite3_0-3.21.0-1
  libvarnam-devel-3.2.6-1bl1
  libvarnam3-3.2.6-1bl1
  pkg-config-0.29.1-1
  ruby-2.3.6-1

Build requirements:
(besides corresponding -devel packages)
  binutils-2.29-1
  cmake-3.6.2-1
  cygport-0.31.1-1
  gcc-core-7.4.0-1
  make-4.2.1-2
  ninja-1.8.2-2
  ruby-2.3.6-1

Canonical website:
  https://github.com/varnamproject/libvarnam

Canonical download:
  https://github.com/varnamproject/libvarnam/archive/v3.2.6.tar.gz

-------------------------------------------

Build instructions:
  1. unpack libvarnam-3.2.6-X-src.tar.xz
  2. if you use setup to install this src package,
     it will be unpacked under /usr/src automatically
        % cd /usr/src
        % cygport ./libvarnam-3.2.6-X.cygport all

This will create:
  /usr/src/libvarnam-3.2.6-X-src.tar.xz
  /usr/src/libvarnam-3.2.6-X.tar.xz
  /usr/src/libvarnam3-3.2.6-X.tar.xz
  /usr/src/libvarnam-devel-3.2.6-X.tar.xz

-------------------------------------------

Files included in the binary package:

(libvarnam)
  /usr/bin/varnamc
  /usr/lib/varnamruby.rb
  /usr/share/doc/Cygwin/libvarnam.README
  /usr/share/doc/libvarnam/AUTHORS
  /usr/share/doc/libvarnam/ChangeLog
  /usr/share/doc/libvarnam/LICENSE.txt
  /usr/share/doc/libvarnam/README.md
  /usr/share/man/man1/varnamc.1.gz
  /usr/share/varnam/vst/ml.vst

(libvarnam3)
  /usr/bin/cygvarnam-3.dll

(libvarnam-devel)
  /usr/include/libvarnam/api.h
  /usr/include/libvarnam/deps/sqlite3.h
  /usr/include/libvarnam/deps/uthash.h
  /usr/include/libvarnam/langcodes.h
  /usr/include/libvarnam/result-codes.h
  /usr/include/libvarnam/util.h
  /usr/include/libvarnam/varnam.h
  /usr/include/libvarnam/varray.h
  /usr/include/libvarnam/vtypes.h
  /usr/include/libvarnam/vutf8.h
  /usr/lib/libvarnam.dll.a
  /usr/lib/pkgconfig/varnam.pc

